  "format": "Longtime producer Bobby Wagner gets a send-off, and he picks the movies: Shrek and Shrek 2. Sean, Amanda, and Bobby run through his seven years on the show, then argue about what a Scottish ogre, two Smash Mouth songs, and a Hallelujah montage did to a generation.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The ‘Shrek’ Pod",
      "note": "Bobby Wagner's send-off pick",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Shrek",
          "year": 2001,
          "note": "Bobby's send-off choice: the movie he grew up rewatching on other kids' DVD players, and his gateway to Eddie Murphy, who plays Donkey. DreamWorks' fairy-tale spoof, loosely adapted from William Steig's book, was originally optioned by Steven Spielberg and set to star Chris Farley, who recorded most of Shrek's voice before he died. Mike Myers took over and, late in production, insisted on redoing the whole thing in a Scottish accent, reportedly costing close to half a million dollars in reanimation. Bobby's theory: this is where movies and memes fused, and the uncanny early-2000s CG is part of why Shrek's face still fills every meme format. The gang dwells on the Gen X soundtrack: Smash Mouth's 'I'm a Believer' and 'All Star,' a Joan Jett needle drop, John Cale singing 'Hallelujah.' It won the first-ever Best Animated Feature Oscar over Monsters, Inc. and Jimmy Neutron."
        },
        {
          "title": "Shrek 2",
          "year": 2004,
          "note": "Slicker, better animated, and to Sean and Amanda a little less fun than the first, missing some of the manic, Zucker-Abrams joke-a-minute energy. Bobby had never seen it before this rewatch, only the memes. Highlights: Antonio Banderas' Puss in Boots, Fairy Godmother running a Goop-like wellness-and-love-potion factory (Sean's bit: Shrek 2 invented Goop), and a soundtrack running from Counting Crows' 'Accidentally in Love' to Nick Cave to a Banderas/Murphy cover of 'Livin' la Vida Loca.' Also home to the deeply upsetting stretch where Shrek turns into a swole 'hottest guy on earth' who looks like he came off a steroid cycle."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
